    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Are you suggesting this would then be a Bazel 'visibility' specific issue and not core itself? I have indeed set the default visibility for all my BUILD files (and WORKSPACE) to `public`. So would this then be a matter of listing these files under `srcs` or `deps` in the relevant target's build rules in the core BUILD file (currently at the project root)? If so, I can try and find out which targets these would belong to.\r\n\r\nI'm not much familiar with `core` code, but I initially assumed this could be happening because of the access modifiers or visibility of code for the core targets that I'm using as dependencies."
