    "updated_at": "2018-06-13T18:22:25Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Right - these files inside of the iomgr are set as `srcs`, while they'd need to be put as `hdrs`. The difference between the two is that a file that's in the `hdrs` section can be referenced by another target, while a file in the `srcs` section can only be referenced by the library itself.\r\n\r\nIt was the case before that nobody was supposed to use these files outside of the iomgr itself, but that's no longer the case if you wish to make a cython target that uses them."
  },
